         <div type="commentary">
         	<p><bibl><ptr target="bib:VenkatasubbaAyyar1943_01"/></bibl> notes about A-E, G-H: 
         		<quote>The following seven labels are engraved in archaic Tamil and Grantha characters on a group of rocks, one of which, on account of a natural cavity in it, is locally known as 'Noṇḍi Vīrappaṉ Kudiraitoṭṭi'. The names Kēvādaperundachchaṉ and Kollaṉ Śēmagaṉ found in this place indicate that the persons bearing these names belonged to the artisan class. One of the labels also gives the name Guṇamallaḥ.</quote></p>
         </div>
         	
<div type="bibliography">
   
